cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.PF, cs.CR, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as it discusses the development of a specification for performance testing of ATM switches and networks. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it deals with the user perceived frame-level performance. Additionally, it could be classified under Performance (cs.PF), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories as it involves testing and specification development for performance and security of ATM networks.
